parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Loss of power steering assist
loud popping noise
steering wheel spins freely
steering wheel has excessive play
vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
difficulty turning the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering shaft can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Steering wheel has excessive play
loud knocking noise
steering wheel binds or is difficult to turn
vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
loss of power steering assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering bearing can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Loud grinding or popping noise
steering wheel has excessive play
steering wheel binds or is difficult to turn
vehicle wanders or pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel hub can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Wheel hub broke at the weld
wheel departed from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The sudden and unexpected acceleration can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, resulting in crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently without warning
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck to the floorboard
the vehicle surges forward while brakes are applied
the engine revs at a high rate
and the vehicle fails to respond to brake pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle body failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents. The failure can lead to stuck accelerator pedals, sudden acceleration, and engine revving at high rates.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck to the floorboard
the vehicle surges forward while brakes are applied
the engine revs at a high rate
and the vehicle fails to respond to brake pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake pedal failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The failure can lead to stuck brake pedals, sudden acceleration, and engine revving at high rates.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle fails to respond to brake pedal input
and the vehicle accelerates independently without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's speed, RPM, fuel level, and temperature, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The instrument cluster is completely dark
no lights illuminate except turn signals
speed
RPM
fuel level
and temperature gauges are not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, electrical shorts, and other safety issues, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front passenger side visor light remains illuminated after the visor is closed
causing the visor material to burn
the instrument panel becomes inoperable intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the RPMs increase without the accelerator being applied
the vehicle accelerates when started and placed into drive.
